#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "The Genesis Block"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Bitcoin launches with the mining of the genesis block by Satoshi "
#~ "Nakamoto.{br}There are very few miners in the early days, and it’s possible "
#~ "for solo miners to find blocks frequently with CPUs."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Slush Pool Launches"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "More participants join the network and some begin mining with GPUs, making "
#~ "it increasingly difficult for solo miners to find blocks. To address this, "
#~ "Marek “Slush” Palatinus announces the creation of the Bitcoin.cz cooperative"
#~ " mining pool in a <a>bitcointalk thread</a>. The pool mined 3 blocks in its "
#~ "first 24 hours of operation on December 16th. (Bitcoin.cz was later renamed "
#~ "to Slush Pool in 2016.)"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "The concept of pooled mining had been discussed in the community before the "
#~ "launch of Slush Pool, with a few implementations all launching around the "
#~ "same time. These early pools did not operate for long before <a>shutting "
#~ "down</a>, except for the Slush Pool."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid " Braiins is Founded & Slush Pool Grows"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Jan Čapek & Pavel Moravec combine their years of IT experience in the "
#~ "banking & embedded engineering industries to start Braiins with a focus on "
#~ "embedded software R&D."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Embedded devices engineer and father of Braiins OS firmware and BOSminer "
#~ "software to replace the outdated and closed CGMiner."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Lead engineer of Slush Pool since 2013, now primarily focused on building "
#~ "hashrate-based market products for the mining industry."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Fun fact:"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Slush Pool was originally operated and funded by Slush. As network traffic "
#~ "to the pool’s servers increased, a 2% fee was introduced to cover the "
#~ "operating costs of running the pool and to address a concern that some "
#~ "community members had that zero fees could lead to greater centralization "
#~ "and less competition. This validated the concept of using a mining pool as a"
#~ " business. As a result, competitors began to emerge, such as DeepBit and BTC"
#~ " Guild, in the Spring of 2011."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Pool Growth & Introduction of Stratum Protocol"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "In March, the web hosting company Linode suffers a hack which leads to "
#~ "<a>the loss</a> of 3094 BTC from the pool wallet. Slush generously covers "
#~ "the loss out of his pocket."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "On September 10th, Slush <a>announces</a> his proposal for a new pooled "
#~ "mining protocol known as Stratum, which helps to address many flaws of the "
#~ "getwork mining protocol. Stratum would go on to become the open standard for"
#~ " pooled mining, helping the industry scale over time."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Braiins Begins Operating Slush Pool"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "In January, the <a>release</a> of the first ASICs by Avalon kickstarts a new"
#~ " era in bitcoin mining."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Marek “Slush” Palatinus launches a new venture separate from Slush Pool "
#~ "called Satoshi Labs, which develops the Trezor hardware wallets. Meanwhile, "
#~ "Braiins acquires a majority stake in Slush Pool and takes over operations "
#~ "and development of the pool."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Braiins Upgrades Pool Infrastructure"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Braiins rewrites Slush Pool’s software to make it more scalable, easier to "
#~ "operate, and secure.{br}Meanwhile, we continue investing in more robust "
#~ "mining infrastructure to accommodate the expanding mining ecosystem across "
#~ "the globe."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "The 1 Milion BTC Milestone"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Slush Pool was the first to reach the 1 million BTC mined milestone and is "
#~ "still the top mining pool in terms of total bitcoins mined at over 1.25 "
#~ "million and counting!"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "bitcoin.cz Becomes Slush Pool"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "The mining community is regularly referring to Bitcoin.cz by its nickname of"
#~ " \"Slush's Pool\", making “Slush Pool” an obvious choice for renaming the "
#~ "pool as it continues to grow internationally."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Braiins Supports BTC, not BCH"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Braiins becomes the first and only pool operator to allow individual miners "
#~ "to participate in bitcoin’s governance by <voting>voting on the "
#~ "controversial issues</voting> of the <segwit>SegWit upgrade</segwit> and a "
#~ "potential block size increase. After the contentious Bitcoin Cash hard fork,"
#~ " Braiins stays focused solely on bitcoin and doesn’t support BCH mining on "
#~ "the pool."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Developing Solutions for Mining Decentralization"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "The Braiins team verifies the capability for overt AsicBoost and is the "
#~ "<asicboos>first pool to add AsicBoost compatibility</asicboos>. Meanwhile, "
#~ "Jan leads a new initiative to offer alternative firmware for the Antminer S9"
#~ " as centralization concerns grow with the Antbleed and covert AsicBoost "
#~ "incidents. In September, Braiins <bos>releases a free and open-source "
#~ "firmware</bos> called Braiins OS for Antminer S9s, enabling overt AsicBoost."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "The Braiins Open-Source Initiative"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "As Braiins OS adoption continues, it becomes clear that CGminer, the mining "
#~ "software used as a base by hardware manufacturers, has become a mess of "
#~ "closed-source forks. To address this, Braiins begins working on BOSminer, a "
#~ "replacement of CGminer written from scratch in Rust language."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Jan and Pavel work with Matt Corallo to <a>publish a detailed specification "
#~ "for Stratum V2</a>, a next-generation pooled mining protocol that solves "
#~ "many of the inefficiencies and security flaws of the original stratum "
#~ "protocol."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Autotuning Firmware to Optimize ASICs"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Braiins launches a commercial variant of the firmware called Braiins OS+ "
#~ "which includes per-chip autotuning to optimize ASIC efficiency at any level "
#~ "of power consumption. The firmware includes a native (<a>partial</a>) "
#~ "Stratum V2 implementation and the team adds Stratum V2 endpoints on Slush "
#~ "Pool, enabling miners to have encrypted V2 connections that are more secure,"
#~ " private, and efficient."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Braiins, which has been the sole operator of Slush Pool since taking a "
#~ "majority stake in 2013, <a>acquires the remaining stake from Marek</a> as he"
#~ " continues to focus on SatoshiLabs."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Slush Pool celebrates its <a>10-year anniversary</a>."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid "Upgrades for Slush Pool and Braiins OS+"
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "Slush Pool gets a major upgrade, enabling an ultra-flexible payout system, "
#~ "customizable reward splitting, and more sophisticated account structuring. "
#~ "The user interface also gets fully redesigned."
#~ msgstr ""

#~ msgctxt "UI"
#~ msgid ""
#~ "The Braiins OS+ team grows rapidly and the list of supported hardware models"
#~ " grows along with it to include the entire X17 generation of Antminers."
#~ msgstr ""

